  1. You’ve performed differential gene expression analyses on a sample. The data is in data3.csv. How many genes can be classified as significantly different at a false discovery rate of 0.05? (2 pts)

  mutate(padjust = p.adjust(pvalue, method = "fdr"))
data3 %>%
  filter(padjust < 0.05) %>%
  nrow()
[1] 3628
data3 %>%
  mutate(signif = ifelse(padjust<0.05, TRUE, FALSE)) %>%
  pull(signif) %>%
  sum()
[1] 3628
  1. Is there a difference in the log2FoldChange.rna between genes that are significantly different and the ones that are not? Perform appropriate statistical test. (1 pt)
ggplot(data3, aes(x = log2FoldChange.rna, color = padjust < 0.05)) +
  geom_density()

data3.sig <- data3 %>%
  filter(padjust < 0.05)
data3.nonsig <- data3 %>%
  filter(padjust >= 0.05)

t.test(data3.sig$log2FoldChange.rna, data3.nonsig$log2FoldChange.rna)
